to the editor re college returns 3 million gift for aids lab news article march 17 among the pleasures of teaching at queens college is the chance to puncture the perception of the college as an institution with as you put it limited science research invariably eminent speakers in our department 's colloquium series express wonderment at the ability of the faculty to carry out wide ranging research at the highest level despite heavy teaching and administrative responsibilities the research labs are magnets for dedicated undergraduate and graduate students and postdoctoral researchers actively engaged in international collaborations at the frontiers of their fields in our own department research in recent years has led to breakthroughs in the fields of photonics magnetism and surface science azriel genack new york march 19 2001 the writer is a physics professor at queens college cuny

